Prepare rice mixes according to package directions. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook the sausage, celery and carrots over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. In a large bowl, combine the sausage mixture, rice mixture and the remaining ingredients. Transfer to two greased 11-in. x 7-in. x 2-in. baking dishes. Cover and bake one casserole at 350 degrees F for 40-45 minutes or until the vegetables are tender. Cover and freeze remaining casserole for up to 3 months. To use frozen casserole: Thaw in the refrigerator. Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes. Bake as directed.